│ has the NSZ fast-math flag. This changes the sign of zero (+0 to -0), which the original select would preserve, │
│ causing Alive2 to report a mismatch. To fix, I will tighten the condition in InstCombineSelect.cpp to not allow │
│ the minnum/maxnum canonicalization solely based on NSZ. Instead, require explicit proof that users ignore zero  │
│ sign (via canIgnoreSignBitOfZero), preventing incorrect -0 propagation.                                         │
│                                                                                                                 │
